Result: false  
Justification:  
The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. Here, the claim is "Brittany is an innovative artist." The P-type arguments all oppose the claim, but their justifications do not collectively cover all possible minimal semantic bases that could support the claim. Specifically, the S-type arguments provide fragments of support (e.g., Brittany's creativity, the conditional linking innovative artists to recognition and masterpieces), but no P-type argument's justification semantically subsumes these supportive fragments. Instead, the P-type arguments focus on contradictions (e.g., lack of passion, no new techniques, no original style) without addressing the possibility that Brittany could still satisfy the conditions for being an innovative artist through other means. Thus, C11 is not satisfied.